I ordered delivery and was given a time estimate of 45-55 minutes. I understand it was raining so I waited until 75 minutes to call and politely ask for a status. The woman on the phone was incredibly rude and before I could finish my sentence she yelled "it's raining! There are so many deliveries. The phone and fax are going crazy. It's raining." I said I understood, but asked if she had any idea on a time estimate. She fired back "the deliveries go North, South, East, and West. They go by what's closest together." I tried to say "okay, thank you" (even though I was incredibly frustrated) but she hung up on me. It was another 45 minutes until the food arrived. It was cold and congealed. The chicken in my chicken lo mein was breaded and soggy. The vegetables were the same color as the noodles and it had zero flavor. After this 2 hour ordeal...I ended up throwing my food away and eating cereal for dinner.

I had originally intended to eat in, but while I was ordering I noticed multiple flies buzzing around the dining area, so I asked for my sweet and sour chicken to go. Now I wish I had just turned around and left, because the food was completely lacking flavor. The sauce could be described as neither sweet nor sour -- it was just orange-colored and wet -- and I lost my appetite well before I could make myself finish the mound of rice, the insipid spring roll, or the weirdly hard veggies. Fortune: You will spend the rest of the day regretting that you ate such mediocre Chinese food. Lucky numbers: 1/5.
